      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAJESTIC LORD (2) did a good job to finish 16 metres from the winner in second on debut last start after breaking in the run over 1690m at this track. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a similar line up so he must be respected. INSULATOR (7) took full advantage of the inside draw when a dominant winner on debut at this course and distance last time out. Primary contender in this comparable race. ZIPPIN PAST (3) is a two-year-old filly from the G A Hunter yard on debut. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Looks to have some ability based on a recent trial win. Any push in betting will add to the confidence. REGAL GALA (1) is stepping out for the first time. By Pastor Stephen and hails from the Chris Angove stable. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Has strong trial form coming into this. Will be right there at the business end.",
